          <li><strong>Expense Ratio:</strong> 0.35%</li>
          <li><strong>Payout Frequency:</strong> Monthly</li>
          <li><strong>Target Volatility:</strong> Lower than the Nasdaq-100 Index</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>Historical Dividend Performance</h2>
      <p>A closer look at the <strong>jepq dividend history</strong> reveals a strong track record of high absolute payouts, though they do fluctuate month-to-month. The size of the monthly distribution is intrinsically linked to the implied volatility of the Nasdaq-100 (often measured by the VXN index). When tech stocks are swinging wildly, option premiums rise, and JEPQ's distributions follow suit. When the market is calm and trending slowly upward, the distributions naturally contract.</p>

