    <section>
      <h2>Comparison to Category Average</h2>
      <p>Compared to other covered call funds, JEPQ is generally considered a higher-beta play than its older sibling, JEPI (which focuses on the S&P 500). Because tech stocks are inherently more volatile than utilities or consumer staples, JEPQ commands higher option premiums and thus consistently posts a higher yield than JEPI.</p>

      <p>However, this higher yield comes with the caveat of capping upside potential during strong bull markets. If the Nasdaq-100 surges 20% in a year, JEPQ will underperform the total return of QQQ because its short call options will be exercised, capping the capital appreciation. The trade-off is the massive 9-11% cash distribution and reduced downside volatility during market corrections.</p>
    </section>

