    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>What is the JEPQ dividend yield history?</summary>
        <p>The <strong>jepq dividend yield history</strong> shows a consistent target range of 9% to 11% annualized. While the exact monthly payout fluctuates with the VIX, the fund has successfully delivered on its high-income mandate since inception.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>When is the JEPQ dividend date?</summary>
        <p>The <strong>jepq dividend date</strong> (ex-dividend) is typically the first business day of each month. To receive the distribution, you must hold the shares prior to this date.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How can I use a JEPQ dividend calculator?</summary>
        <p>A <strong>jepq dividend calculator</strong> is useful for modeling cash flow. Because payouts vary, input a conservative 6-month trailing average for the monthly dividend amount rather than a peak month to avoid overestimating your income.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What was the JEPQ dividend yield 2024?</summary>
        <p>The <strong>jepq dividend yield 2024</strong> hovered around 9.5%, providing a steady monthly income stream to investors while mitigating some of the downside volatility experienced by the broader tech sector.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What should we expect for the JEPQ dividend yield 2025?</summary>
        <p>The <strong>jepq dividend yield 2025</strong> will be determined by tech sector volatility. If the Nasdaq-100 continues to experience moderate to high volatility, option premiums will remain elevated, supporting the fund's double-digit yield target.</p>
